articles.description: Dimencio Vaughn scored 28 points and grabbed a dozen rebounds as Rider staged an improbable comeback, roaring back from 21 points down in the final 10 minutes to post an 89-79 win over Marist Saturday to maintain a share of first place in the Metro...
articles.headline: Rider holds onto MAAC lead, rallies past Marist, 89-79

articles.description: Taylor Johnson scored 21 points and Dartmouth picked up its first conference win, downing Princeton 72-56 on Saturday night, snapping a 10-game skid.
articles.headline: Dartmouth downs Princeton 72-56

images.caption: Big Green holds off Princeton to pick up its first #RoadtoIvyMadness victory of the year
images.name: Dartmouth picks up first Ivy win of the season  - Via Ivy League

articles.description: Nick Mayo scored 18 points, grabbed five rebounds and blocked four shots and Eastern Kentucky made 4 of 6 foul shots down the stretch to hold off Morehead State 75-73 on Saturday night.
articles.headline: E. Kentucky holds off Morehead St.; Mayo scores 18 PTs

articles.description: Tyler Sharpe hit two 3-pointers in the closing minutes Saturday night to secure Northern Kentucky's fifth straight win, an 86-80 victory over Green Bay that moved the Norse into sole possession of first-place in the Horizon League.
articles.headline: Northern Kentucky takes Horizon lead, beats Green Bay 86-80

articles.description: John Dewey III stole an inbound pass and fed Christopher Galbreath Jr. for a layup in the final seconds as Sam Houston State took a 71-69 win over Lamar in Southland Conference play on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Sam Houston St. slips past Lamar 71-69 in final seconds
